&lt;p&gt;As the Accounting Manager, you will play a key role in the close operations and financial reporting for Fanatics’ Betting &amp;amp; Gaming (“FBG”). This is a hands-on role with primary ownership of joint venture and non-controlling interest accounting, consolidation accounting, intercompany activity, and financial/statutory reporting, ensuring the completeness and accuracy of our financials across a complex, multi-entity structure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will serve as a key connector across the organization — partnering with the Sr. Director of Accounting on financial reporting, working closely with Shared Services and Technical Accounting on complex transactions, and collaborating with Finance and business stakeholders to ensure activity is properly captured in the financials. This role offers the opportunity to build deep expertise across consolidation, intercompany accounting, and financial reporting in a fast-growing, regulated environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review journal entries prepared by the Staff Accountant for accuracy, completeness, and proper support prior to posting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own joint venture and non-controlling interest accounting, including NCI allocations and related financial statement presentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the consolidation and elimination process across all FBG legal entities, ensuring intercompany balances are properly reconciled and eliminated each close cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform and review balance sheet reconciliations across assigned areas, monitoring reconciliation status and ensuring timely resolution of open items&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare quarterly flux analysis across key balance sheet and income statement accounts, identifying and explaining significant variances and trends to support financial review&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and review quarterly and annual financial statements in accordance with US GAAP, including state-level reporting requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and strengthen internal controls (including SOX) across consolidation and intercompany accounting pro

